          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin-10mm-Step-1-1612882922253-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> drained chickpeas</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until softened</p><p>Once the tomatoes have softened, add the <strong>vegetable stock </strong>to the pan and cook for 2 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, squeeze the pouch[es] of <strong>cooked brown long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water </strong>all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much of the water out of the spinach as you can, then chop it roughly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Turn the heat down to low and stir through the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed coconut </strong>and<strong> mango chutney</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped spinach</strong>,<strong> </strong>season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>chickpea, spinach & coconut curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2286Step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> chickpea, spinach & coconut curry</strong> over the <strong>brown rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>nigella seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
